َIn loving memory of
The Whytock Family
Richard (Dick), Barbara (Barry), Ruth and Norma
'Sit and rest awhile on your journey up to the top of the hill or down to Stockaree'
Donated by their loving daughter and sister, Edna and the Millar Family"ِ
َKENNETH MCLENNAN HAY, ESQ, B.E.M., K.C.L.J., F.S.A. Scot.
20th FEBRUARY, 1918 22nd SEPTEMBER, 1992.
COMMISSIONER OF THE CLAN HAY 1979-1990.
PRESIDENT OF THE ST ANDREWS SOCIETY OF EDINBURGH.
CHAIRMAN - THE ROYAL CELTIC SOCIETY
A GOVERNOR OF BENENDEN HOSPITAL.
ERECTED BY HIS FAMILY, HIS MANY FRIENDS
AND THE SOCIETIES AND TRUSTS THAT HE SERVED SO WELL.
SERVA IUGUM"ْ
